\int \frac{17x^2}{(x+1)(x^2+1)}\, dx
\frac{17x^2}{(x+1)(x^2+1)}= \frac{A}{x+1} +\frac{Bx+C}{x^2+1}
x=-1
A
A=17/2
(-17/4)(-\ln|x^2+1|-2\ln|x+1|+2\arctan(x))
A = \dfrac{17}2
A(x^2 + 1) + (Bx + C) (x + 1) = 17x^2
\underbrace{\frac{17}2}_{A} + C = 0 \iff C = -\frac{17}{2}
x = 1
\underbrace{17}_{2A}+ 2B + 2C = 17 \iff 2B + 2C = 0 \iff B = -C = \frac{17}{2}
x=i
B
C
Bi+C=-\frac{17}{i+1}=\frac{17}2(i-1)
\int\frac{dx}{x^2+1}=\arctan x+C
